📍 Mohali :- Irked over water logged for five days, residents of Willington Residency in Sector 117, Mohali, filled water in a tanker and dumped it at the office of the promoter on Thursday. The residents alleged that despite numerous complaints, the promoter of TDIdid not act to drain the water out of the residential society.

The rainwater entered the houses and shops of the residents in the housing society, they alleged.The videos went viral of the residents and shopkeepers throwing the water tanker using a hose pipe into the corporate office of TDI and using buckets full of water spilled over furniture, office tables, and other office items.

The residents alleged that the drainage system of the society had crashed and there had been massive water logging, but the promoter was least bothered to get it cleared and residents feared outbreak of an epidemic.
